div1.p: IN THE DISTRICT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NORTHERN DIVISION
In the Matter of the Application of CHIN WAH HING For a Writ of Habeas Corpus.| No. 3378 WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS.
THE PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA, to Henry M. White, Commissioner of Immigration at Seattle, Washington:

WE COMMAND YOU, that you have the body of CHIN DOE TUNG by you imprisoned and detained, as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention, by whatsoever name the said Chin Doe Tung shall be called or charged, before the Hon. Jeremiah Neterer, United States District Judge for the Western District of Washington, Northern Division, at the United States Court Room, Postoffice, Custom House and United States Court Building, in the City of Seattle, in the Northern Division of said Western District of Washington. on the 17th day of July, A.D. 1916, at ten o'clock A.M., to do and receive what shall then and there concerning him, the said Chin Doe Tung. And have you then and there this Writ.

WITNESS the Hon. Jeremiah Neterer, Judge of the United States District Court for the Western District of Washington, Northern Division, this 8th day of July, in the year of our Lord one thousand nine hundred and sixteen.
Frank L. Crosby, Clerk By Ed rm Lastern CLERK.
